						<provenance>The "Pote Collection" arrived in England from India in <date
								calendar="#Gregorian">1790</date> and was divided between the
							Colleges of Eton and King's, Cambridge, with the first half
							alphabetically going to King's. Both halves of the collection are now
							housed in Cambridge University Library on permanent loan. Most if not
							all of the manuscripts had previously been owned by <persName
								key="person_7537069" role="fmo" change="#role-assignment">Colonel
								Antoine-Louis Henri Polier (1741–1795)</persName>. </provenance>
						<acquisition>Gift of <persName key="person_f5696" role="fmo"
								change="#role-assignment">Edward Ephraim Pote (d.1832)</persName> in
								<date calendar="#Gregorian">1788</date>.</acquisition>
					</history>
